# CLAUDE.md

Behavioral guidelines to reduce common LLM coding mistakes. Merge with project-specific instructions as needed.

**Tradeoff:** These guidelines bias toward caution over speed. For trivial tasks, use judgment.

## 0. Startup — DO THIS FIRST

**Before any tool call or response**, execute all three steps:

1. **Search past work**: `mcp__mem-search-lite__search(query="<task in 3-5 words>", limit=5)`.
2. **Read relevant memory files**: The SessionStart hook injects a live memory index with descriptions. If this task matches any listed topic, `Read` that file.
3. **Match skill by task pattern** — invoke `Skill` BEFORE acting:

| User says... | Invoke this skill |
|---|---|
| "bug/error/crash/报错/出问题" | `systematic-debugging` |
| "implement/add/build/实现/添加/做" | `test-driven-development` |
| "design/design audit/audit/审查设计/检查UI" | `design-is` |
| "plan/设计/方案" (before coding) | `writing-plans` |
| "review this PR"/"审查PR" | `pr-review` |
| "done/fixed/complete/搞定" | `verification-before-completion` |
| "create PPT/做PPT/presentation" | `ppt-master` |
| "summarize/总结" | `summarize` |
| "skill accuracy/trigger review/skillopt" | `skillopt` |
| "permission/settings/config/设置/权限" | `update-config` |
| "slow/optimize/perf/性能" | `performance` |
| Multiple independent tasks | `dispatching-parallel-agents` |
| `[MultiAgent Hook]` appears in context | **DISPATCH PARALLEL AGENTS** — use Agent tool |
| "multiagent miss/false positive" | Record to `multiagent-feedback/feedback.md` |
| "security/安全" + review | `security-review` |
| "refactor/simplify/review code quality" | `code-simplifier` (Rust) |

**Rule: when a pattern matches, invoke the skill. Don't deliberate. Invoke first, then decide if it was the right call.** Skipping = repeated mistakes.

## 1. Think Before Coding

**Don't assume. Don't hide confusion. Surface tradeoffs.**

Before implementing:
- State your assumptions explicitly. If uncertain, ask.
- If multiple interpretations exist, present them - don't pick silently.
- If a simpler approach exists, say so. Push back when warranted.

## 2. Simplicity First

**Minimum code that solves the problem. Nothing speculative.**

- No features beyond what was asked.
- No abstractions for single-use code.
- No error handling for impossible scenarios.

## 3. Surgical Changes

**Touch only what you must. Clean up only your own mess.**

- Don't "improve" adjacent code, comments, or formatting.
- Don't refactor things that aren't broken.
- Match existing style, even if you'd do it differently.

## 4. Goal-Driven Execution

**Define success criteria. Loop until verified.**

For multi-step tasks, state a brief plan:
```
1. [Step] → verify: [check]
2. [Step] → verify: [check]
3. [Step] → verify: [check]
```

## 5. Global Environment Preferences

- Python: default to the specified Python environment. Set `HARNESS_PYTHON` env var for harness scripts.
- Git clone location: clone repositories to a sensible drive/location.
- No C: drive downloads: NEVER install, extract, or download large files to C: drive.

## 6. Automatic Memory & TrainingLoop System

Three training dimensions share one unified feedback system at `training-loop/`:

| Dimension | Focus | Feedback Format |
|---|---|---|
| SkillOpt | Skill trigger accuracy | `### Miss` / `### False Positive` |
| MultiAgentOpt | Agent dispatch accuracy | `### Miss` / `### False Positive` |
| ToolCallOpt | Tool call pattern quality | `### Positive` / `### Negative` |

### 6.1 Memory System — Two-Tier Write Architecture

**Tier 1 (auto): Session Log.** Every session with substantive work gets a 1-line log in SQLite.

**Tier 2 (manual): Structured Memory.** Only when user explicitly says "记住" / "remember this". Write to `memory/` directory.

### 6.2 TrainingLoop — Unified Feedback System

**Workflow:**
1. `training-collect.sh` (Stop hook) syncs all 3 dimensions to unified meta.json
2. `session-start-inject.sh` reads unified meta → single threshold alert block
3. `post-task-detect.sh` prompts TrainingLoop reflection on completion
4. All feedback writes to `training-loop/feedback.md` (one file, three ## sections)
5. At 3 signals per dimension, SessionStart injects alert

**Explicit triggers:** Say "skill miss"/"skill false positive", "multiagent miss"/"multiagent fp", "toolcall observation" to record.

### 6.3 Multi-Agent Detection (multiagent-detect.sh)

Two-phase heuristic scoring system detects complex tasks and suggests parallel agent dispatch.

- **Phase 1**: Fast keyword/pattern matching (filters ~95% chat, zero cost)
- **Phase 2**: Structural analysis (task verbs, file refs, tech boundaries)
- Soft suggestion only — AI decides whether to dispatch.
- Feedback via "multiagent miss" / "multiagent false positive".

### 6.4 Harness Automation

| Event | Script | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| SessionStart | `health-check.sh` | Validates system integrity |
| SessionStart | `security-audit.sh` | Lightweight security checks |
| SessionStart | `session-start-inject.sh` | Injects memory index + 3-step checklist |
| UserPromptSubmit | `multiagent-detect.sh` | Detects complex tasks → parallel agent suggestion |
| UserPromptSubmit | `post-task-detect.sh` | Detects completion → write reminders |
| Stop | `skillopt-collect.sh` | Syncs feedback counters → threshold alerts |
| (on-demand) | `auto-summary.py` | Writes 1-line session log to SQLite |

**DISABLED_HOOKS**: Temporarily disable hooks via `export DISABLED_HOOKS="multiagent-detect,post-task-detect"`.
